PACIFIC AMERICAN FISHERIES, Inc., a Corporation, Appellant, v. UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION COMMISSION OF ALASKA, and Richard Hardcastle, Mildred E. Herman and John Cauble, as Members of said Commission, Appellee. No. 11108. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 12, 1945. Marshall P. Madison, Francis R. Kirk-ham, and Melvin E. Mensor, all of San Francisco, Cal., and H. L. Faulkner, of Juneau, Alaska, for appellant. Ralph J. Rivers, Atty. Gen. for Alaska, for appellees.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Ordered motion of appellant to dismiss appeal herein granted, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
